Interface GameState

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<State>, Graphvizable, State
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Checkers, GameStateImpl, HelloWorldGameState, NimState

    public interface GameState
extends State
    An abstract state in some game tree search problem.
    Author:
    Przemysław Klęsk (wi.zut.edu.pl), Marcin Korzeń (wi.zut.edu.pl)

      • isVisited

        boolean isVisited()
        Returns boolean value indicating whether this state is flagged as visited during search. It is possible that copies of the same state in different places of search tree will have different 'visited' flags. Some of copies might be generated but cut off, or read from the transposition table.
        Returns:
        boolean value indicating whether this state is flagged as visited during search

        Parameters:

      • isReadFromTranspositionTable

        boolean isReadFromTranspositionTable()
        Returns boolean value indicating whether this state instance is flagged as read (evaluated) from transposition table. It is possible that copies of the same state in different places of search tree will have different 'readFromTranspositionTable' flags. This flag is memorized only for informative purposes (in particular for Graphviz functionality).
        Returns:
        boolean value indicating whether this state is flagged as read from transposition table
